Gunmen numbering five suspected to be bandits reportedly invaded the home of Mr Olanrewaju Suraju, Chairman of HEDA Resource Centre in Lagos and carted away five phones and other valuable items. The assailants who were said to be heavily armed with guns, knives and other dangerous weapons also threatened to kill Mr Suraju, physically hit him and his wife who are both hospitalised. They also went with a Toyota Corolla 2014 car, jewelries, ATM cards, cars keys, Bank Tokens, office documents among other valuables belonging to Mr Suraju and his family. According to a statement issued in Lagos by the Human and Environmental Development Agenda (HEDA Resource Centre) and signed by its Executive Secretary, Mr Sulaimon Arigbabu, the assailants who were caught on CCTV camera invaded Mr Suraju’s home in Lagos at around 2:15am on Monday, 28th March 2022, breached the Estate’s Security and burgled the security features in his house with sophisticated tools. “The assailants, who invaded only Mr. Suraju’s home out of other 220 buildings in the estate, collected all valuable items in the house and coerced Mr Suraju to provide all his security details including phone passwords, bank log-in details, laptops passwords, among others. The assailants then immediately gained access to his email, phone numbers including WhatsApp and other messaging platforms as well as bank platforms,’’ Arigbabu said.